intro:
Africa is home to some of the deadliest creatures of all, and in this series, you'll see them.
S5 E1 - Lethal Strike
Some of the most dangerous of Africa's predators are mostly overlooked, preferring to remain hidden until the very last second. For Africa's snakes, chemical weaponry is the name of the game. Africa's Deadliest: snakes follows the continent's apex predators, proving that Africa's beauty only runs skin deep. Behind the veil of greens and glittering golds, lurk perfect killers.
S5 E2 - Fangs that Kill
In Africa the battle for survival rages across some of the most extreme environments on the planet. Here, predators have adapted some of the deadliest weaponry on earth. Large carnivores such as hyenas and wild dogs - equipped with savage canines and unrivalled tenacity - are capable of tearing their prey apart in seconds.
S5 E3 - Killers of the Deep
Of all of Africa's predators, perhaps the most hair-raising of all are not on land, but in the sea. Ancient hunters of the deep, having perfected their game millennia ago, sharks are the undisputed rulers of the seas. Of the 3 most deadly sharks in the world - the Tiger shark, the Bull shark and the infamous Great white - the African coastline is home to all 3 of them.
